
  
  <section>xml:id="Scale-shapes" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
    <title>Scale Shapes</title>
  <introduction>
    <p> It is relatively easy to learn (or build) Scales and Chords on the Chromatic Button Accordion because the Keyboard is laid out in such a fashion that the physical relationship between notes remains constant. Once you know the "shape" of a particular scale or chord on the keyboard, that shape can be moved elsewhere on the keyboard and provide  chords and scales in all the other Keys.</p>
    
  </introduction>

 <p>Moveable Major Scales on Treble C System Keyboard. Tonic starts scale on Columns 1,2 or 3.</p>
<p>
  Each moveable scale can be moved up and down the keyboard or 1 or 2 columns to the left
</p>
